
CITADEL AGRICULTURAL CORE: MASTER ARCHITECTURAL BLUEPRINTSystem Revision: 2.0 (Integrated External Waste & Hybrid Energy Node)1. Spatial & Structural ArchitecturePhysical Profile: Cylindrical, earth-sheltered subterranean layout.Dimensions: 30 ft Diameter, 30 ft Total Height.Subterranean Depth: 20 ft underground (67% total structure mass).Structural Walls: 10–14 inch reinforced concrete walls designed to resist lateral earth and subterranean hydrostatic pressure.Foundation: 12-inch reinforced concrete floor slab tied directly to structural walls to prevent buoyant lifting in high water tables.Productive Space Allocation: 3,220 total square feet of productive surface area.Floor 2 (Top/Ground Level): Ample natural light from a 30 ft concave glass ceiling and 8–12 vertical clear polycarbonate tubes.Floor 1 (Middle Level): 752 sq ft wall shelving, 564 sq ft dark zones. Requires total artificial lighting support.Subfloor (Bottom Level): 400 sq ft clean zone dedicated strictly to seed germination and clean vermicomposting. Completely isolated from external waste nodes.2. Closed-Loop Hydrological SystemPrimary Catchment: 700 sq ft rainwater harvest area.Annual Collection: ~15,750 gallons (calculated at 36 inches of annual rainfall).System Efficiency: 95% efficient aeroponic loops with a net annual system water loss of 8,300 gallons.Cistern Capacity: 20,000-gallon internal stabilization cistern.System Initialization: Filled completely to capacity via conventional methods during startup to establish thermal mass and instant operating loops.Drought Buffer: Holds a net annual surplus of ~7,000–7,450 gallons, exceeding the 60-day absolute drought safety window.3. Hybrid Power & Lighting InfrastructureThermal Regulation: Passive geothermal earth-sheltering holds a baseline 55°F environment. Ground-source heat pumps provide active climate micro-adjustments.Electrical Demand: Subterranean LED grow lights require a continuous 30 Kilowatt (kW) electrical draw for 12–16 hour photoperiods.Power Solution A (Solar Array): A 45 kW DC solar array consisting of approximately 113 commercial 400W panels. Occupies 2,500 sq ft of nearby surface area.Power Solution B (Biogas Engine): A 10 kW continuous-duty biogas generator engine providing baseline nighttime power and reducing battery bank size dependencies.[45 kW Solar Array] -------\
